==English==

===Etymology===
[[Middle French]] '''''denoter''''' from [[Latin]] '''''denotare'''''; '''''de-''''' "complete" and '''''notare''''' "to mark (out)"

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|denot|e}}

# To indicate; to [[mark]].
#: ''The yellow [[blaze]]s '''denote''' the trail.''
# To make [[overt]].
#: ''The tears '''denoted''' her true feelings.''
# To refer to literally; to convey [[meaning]].
#: ''"Pre-" '''denotes''' "before."''

